TextChange: Cooperation and competition are needed for people to be successful. I think that some people are more motivated by being able to work along side of other people and than some need that competition to drive them forward. I will talk about how both cooperation and competition are needed for success.\nCooperation is needed for success sometimes because people don't always have the answers. Sometimes people need to work together to come up with a workable solution to problems that arise. When these people can come together to accomplish something they both succeed. Then on the other hand sometimes that drive to outperform someone helps drive that person's success.
